message: Together, Harold and Smith have trained 14 other volunteers to canvas hotels in the Coulee Region, alerting them to signs of human trafficking.  According to Smith, one of the telltale signs of trafficking is a female, often 12-14 years of age traveling with an older "Boyfriend." Smith said that many trafficking connections often get started on Facebook using the Messenger app.

attachments.media_description: Coulee Region's Church Women United takes aim at trafficking
